      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "There was plenty of merit in last week's performance of FARFALLA STRIDE (7) when she drew wide and raced parked but fought on for second at this circuit and distance. Draws a little lower so has winning claims. NAMAKA (10) will be at peak fitness now and has her hoof on the till after back-to-back placings at this circuit and distance, both from similar barriers to this. GIPSY PRINCESS (11) wasn't disgraced in last week's Sibelia Stakes and will find this easier. She draws out but overcame a wide barrier when scoring three back at this circuit and distance. MISSAUDACIOUS (8) was good here last start when she raced parked but boxed on to be beaten only 1.4m into third. ISLA ROCHELLE (5) draws lower than in last week's fourth and placed in both rounds of the Riverina Championships prior. Contender.",
